images/princessa.jpeg',NULL,33.98400000,35.63300000,'+9619765432'),(212,'hotels','Budget','? Terrebrune Hotel','Terrebrune Hotel','Very well preserved hotel and everything seems new. Good restaurant with a rich variety for breakfast. They have a nice and clean outdoor pool.','Clean and modern hotel with pool.','/images/terr.jpeg',NULL,33.91100000,35.66210000,'+9611459870'),(213,'hotels','Budget','? Ahiram Hotel','Ahiram Hotel','Each room is designed to be cozy and intimate, with comfortable bedding and modern amenities.','Cozy rooms with modern amenities.','/images/ahiram.jpeg',NULL,34.25500000,35.65800000,'+9619456789'),(301,'restaurants','Lebanese','? Em Sherif','Em Sherif','Step into a realm of culinary splendor where Lebanese traditions unfold with a timeless Em Sherif touch and flair.','A refined Lebanese restaurant combining culinary tradition with timeless elegance.','/images/sherif.jpeg',NULL,33.88860000,35.49550000,'+9611206206'),(302,'restaurants','Lebanese','? Westwood Valley','Westwood Valley \"Farcha\"','Enjoy the traditional food, the music and the alcohol along with all you need to experience love.','Tradition, music and love in an unforgettable natural atmosphere.','/images/farcha.jpeg',NULL,33.91120000,35.60750000,'+9611945678'),(303,'restaurants','Lebanese','? Lakkis Farm','Lakkis Farm','Lakkis Farms bring farm-to-table dining, delicious dairy products, and meat to their guests.','Farm-to-table dining with dairy products and meat.','/images/lakkis.jpeg',NULL,33.82310000,35.90230000,'+9618677788'),(304,'restaurants','Lebanese','? Mersal','Mersal','Nestled in the charming city of Zahlé, MERSAL is a celebrated Arab restaurant that invites tourists to indulge in the rich tapestry of Lebanese cuisine.','Arabic restaurant in Zahlé, rich in Lebanese flavors.','/images/mersal.jpeg',NULL,33.84620000,35.90240000,'+9618832123'),(305,'restaurants','Lebanese','? Al Shams','Al Shams','Authentic cuisine woven into tradition. Nurturing care and unwavering passion. Al Shams is more than just a space to experience life.','Authentic cuisine woven with tradition. More than just a restaurant.','/images/shams.jpeg',NULL,33.85010000,35.90210000,'+9618999456'),(306,'restaurants','Lebanese','? Ahwet Zaytouna','Ahwet Zaytouna','Ahwet Zeitouna embodies the Lebanese neighborhood café. It is a sought destination any time of the day, for breakfast, lunch, or dinner.','Lebanese neighborhood café ideal at any time of day.','/images/zeytouna.jpeg',NULL,33.88840000,35.49580000,'+9611981123'),(307,'restaurants','Lebanese','? Tawlet Ammiq','Tawlet Ammiq','Tawlet Ammiq is Souk el Tayeb\'s second farmer\'s\' kitchen nestled in the heart of the ancient Ammiq village, boasting panoramic views.','Farm cuisine with panoramic views in Ammiq.','/images/tawle.jpeg',NULL,33.77650000,35.84010000,'+9618893344'),(308,'restaurants','Lebanese','? Babel','Babel','Original and very tasty food and unusual drinks at this contemporary Middle Eastern restaurant with a delightful terrace.','Modern oriental cuisine with unique presentation.','/images/babel.jpeg',NULL,33.90110000,35.51350000,'+9611445566'),(309,'restaurants','Italian','? Portofino','Portofino','Portofino\'s Italian LLC is an Italian restaurant in Lebanon, that can make you feel like you are eating in Italy with all the delicious dishes.','Italy in the heart of Lebanon, with authentic dishes.','/images/portofino.jpeg',NULL,33.89810000,35.50010000,'+9617000111'),(310,'restaurants','Italian','? Westwood Valley Omnya','Westwood Valley Omnya','The restaurant prides itself on serving authentic Italian cuisine, prepared with fresh, locally sourced ingredients.','Authentic and local Italian cuisine.','/images/omnya.jpeg',NULL,33.90050000,35.61000000,'+96171223344'),(311,'restaurants','Italian','? Gavi','Gavi','Gavi is a stylish and authentic Italian restaurant that seamlessly merges traditional dishes with modern flair.','Refined style, traditional and modern dishes.','/images/gavi.png',NULL,33.89450000,35.51230000,'+96176881234'),(312,'restaurants','Italian','? Tavolina','Tavolina','At Tavolina, inside, it\'s cozy and peaceful, and outside, it\'s lively and refreshing. Both create the perfect mood for the delicious food.','Cozy atmosphere and delicious food.','/images/tavolina.jpeg',NULL,33.89330000,35.49440000,'+96178889911'),(313,'restaurants','French','? Le Ciel','Le Ciel','Admire panoramic views over Beirut\'s skyline, while enjoying refined cuisine prepared by expert chefs.','Panoramic view of Beirut with refined cuisine.','/images/ciel.webp',NULL,33.88700000,35.48200000,'+9611345678'),(314,'restaurants','French','? Centrale','Centrale','The elegant ground-floor restaurant serves delicious French cuisine, with seasonable dishes and a fittingly varying menu.','Elegant French cuisine with seasonal menu.','/images/centrale.jpeg',NULL,33.89480000,35.48490000,'+9611456789'),(315,'restaurants','Street','? Eddy\'s Street Food','Eddy\'s Street Food','Famous for the signature Kaake Trabolsiye Aal Fahem, a traditional Lebanese bread grilled to perfection, Eddy\'s Street Food is a must-visit.','Kaake Trabolsiye grilled to perfection.','/images/eddy.webp',NULL,33.90010000,35.47010000,'+9611231231'),(316,'restaurants','Fast','? Roadster Diner','Roadster Diner','Experience diverse flavors and exceptional service at Roadster Diner, where every meal is a celebration of taste and hospitality.','Varied flavors and exceptional service.','/images/roadster.jpeg',NULL,33.89110000,35.49020000,'+9611900900'),(317,'restaurants','Fast','? Swiss Butter','Swiss Butter','Your friendly neighborhood steakhouse. A place for everyone to come in and enjoy a good meal.','Steakhouse for all tastes.','/images/swiss.jpeg',NULL,33.89550000,35.50550000,'+9611555566'),(318,'restaurants','Fast','? Boneless 28','Boneless 28','Explore the delicious offerings at Boneless 28. From curly fries to honey mustard burgers, satisfy your cravings with our flavorful food.','Burgers, twisted fries and more.','/images/boneless.jpeg',NULL,33.88990000,35.49390000,'+9617777788'),(319,'restaurants','Fast','? Junkies Food','Junkies Food','Fast, fresh and famous for wraps and burgers.','Quick and delicious wraps and burgers.','/images/junkies.jpeg',NULL,33.89980000,35.49870000,'+9616111222'),(320,'restaurants','Fast','? Lemon Melon','Lemon Melon','At Lemon Melon, we\'re passionate about crafting delicious bites using the finest ingredients, delivering a satisfying and memorable experience.','Gourmet snacks with quality ingredients.','/images/lemon.webp',NULL,33.90330000,35.49000000,'+9611333444'),(321,'restaurants','Fast','? Zaatar w Zeit','Zaatar w Zeit','Even if the eater has never tried Lebanese street food, Zaatar W Zeit has something for everyone with approachable ingredients and clear menu descriptions.','Lebanese street food accessible to all.','/images/zeit.jpeg',NULL,33.88660000,35.49590000,'+9611777888'),(401,'activities','Outdoor','Mountain Hiking','Mountain Hiking in Lebanon','Experience breathtaking trails in the Chouf and Tannourine.','Mountain hiking in Lebanon is one of the most rewarding ways to experience the country\'s breathtaking natural beauty and cultural richness. With two main mountain ranges—the Lebanon and Anti-Lebanon mountains—running parallel to the coast, hikers are spoiled with stunning panoramic views, fresh mountain air, and diverse ecosystems. Trails range from easy scenic walks to challenging treks reaching altitudes above 2,500 meters. Some of the most popular destinations include the Qadisha Valley, a deep gorge carved into the mountains, home to ancient Christian monasteries built into the cliffs; the Tannourine Cedar Forest Reserve, where trails wind through centuries-old cedar trees and limestone formations; and the Chouf Biosphere Reserve, Lebanon\'s largest protected area, where you can hike for hours across forests, meadows, and villages. Hiking in Lebanon isn\'t just about the physical activity—it\'s also a cultural experience. You pass through traditional mountain villages, encounter shepherds and farmers, and enjoy homemade food in local guesthouses. The unique geography of Lebanon allows you to see the Mediterranean Sea from mountain peaks, making every hike feel surreal. Whether you\'re watching the sun rise from the summit of Mount Sannine or exploring snow-covered trails in winter, mountain hiking in Lebanon is a journey into the heart of nature and heritage.','/images/hike.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(402,'activities','Outdoor','Beach Relaxation','Beach Relaxation','Enjoy the Mediterranean coast from Tyre to Batroun.','Lebanon\'s Mediterranean coastline offers an incredible beach experience, blending natural beauty, historic charm, and modern comfort. Stretching over 200 kilometers from Naqoura in the south to Akkar in the north, the Lebanese coast is dotted with sandy beaches, rocky coves, and vibrant beach clubs. One of the most iconic beach destinations is Batroun, a charming coastal town famous for its natural sea wall, clear blue waters, and lively beach bars. Byblos (Jbeil) offers a perfect mix of history and relaxation, where you can sunbathe by the sea just steps away from ancient Phoenician ruins. Tyre (Sour) in the south is home to some of the country\'s most pristine public beaches, with wide stretches of golden sand and calm, shallow waters ideal for families. In Jiyyeh and Rmeileh, you\'ll find luxurious resorts alongside more rustic, natural spots perfect for a quiet retreat. What makes Lebanon\'s beach scene so special is the diversity: you can enjoy a party atmosphere with DJs and cocktails, or a tranquil moment watching the sunset with your feet in the sand. The warm Mediterranean climate ensures a long beach season, and the proximity of sea and mountains means you can swim in the morning and hike in the afternoon. Whether you\'re snorkeling in rocky inlets, paddleboarding along the coast, or simply soaking up the sun, Lebanon\'s beaches offer unforgettable moments for every traveler.','/images/beachh.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(403,'activities','Outdoor','Caving','Caving in Lebanon','A mountainous and rocky country composed primarily of limestone, Lebanon offers exciting opportunities for caving.','Caving in Lebanon opens the door to a hidden underground world filled with wonder, mystery, and natural artistry. The country\'s diverse geology, especially its abundant limestone formations, has given rise to a wide array of caves, some easily accessible and others reserved for more experienced adventurers. Jeita Grotto, Lebanon\'s most famous cave system, is a national treasure and a must-see destination. Divided into upper and lower galleries, it features colossal stalactites and stalagmites, shimmering underground lakes, and cathedral-like chambers carved by nature over millions of years. Beyond Jeita, Lebanon hosts a variety of lesser-known caves waiting to be explored. Afqa Cave, the legendary source of the Adonis River, combines mythology and nature in a dramatic cliffside setting. Roueiss Cave in the Baatara region leads to the famous Baatara Gorge Waterfall, a surreal site where a river falls through a triple natural bridge into a deep sinkhole. Caving in Lebanon is not just about sightseeing—it\'s a thrilling exploration that connects you to the geological forces that shaped the land. Some caves require rappelling, crawling, and navigating narrow passages, making them perfect for adrenaline-seekers and spelunking enthusiasts. Others are family-friendly and include guided tours with lighting and walkways. Whether you\'re a first-time visitor marveling at nature\'s artwork or an experienced explorer seeking uncharted chambers, Lebanon\'s caves offer unforgettable adventures and a deep sense of awe beneath the surface of this ancient land.','/images/cave.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(404,'activities','Outdoor','Camping','Camping in Lebanon','More and more camping options are emerging in Lebanon, and many existing sites are simply spectacular.','Camping in Lebanon is a magical experience that lets you immerse yourself in the country\'s natural beauty while enjoying a peaceful escape from urban life. From the mountains to the forests and even the coastline, there are countless scenic spots to pitch a tent or park a camper. In the Chouf Cedar Reserve, campers can sleep beneath majestic cedar trees, surrounded by wildlife and the cool breeze of the highlands. Sites like Tannourine and Laqlouq offer breathtaking views, clean air, and the opportunity to stargaze far from the city lights. For a more adventurous experience, you can camp along hiking trails or at the edge of dramatic cliffs overlooking the Qadisha Valley. In contrast, coastal camping spots in Chekka, Rmeileh, or Anfeh allow you to sleep to the sound of waves and wake up to sunrise over the sea. Many campgrounds in Lebanon now offer eco-friendly amenities, including wooden cabins, bonfire areas, and shared kitchens, making camping accessible even for first-timers. What truly sets camping in Lebanon apart is the sense of community and hospitality. Locals often invite campers to share meals, tell stories around the fire, or guide them through nearby villages and trails. Whether you\'re looking for solitude in nature or a social outdoor adventure, camping in Lebanon is a soulful and refreshing experience that reconnects you with the land, the sky, and the simple joys of life.','/images/camp.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(405,'activities','Outdoor','Cycling','Cycling in Lebanon','Lebanon\'s rugged mountains, hills, valleys, and its spectacular scenery immersed in history, make for some truly unique mountain biking opportunities.','Cycling in Lebanon is a thrilling way to explore the country\'s diverse landscapes, offering something for everyone—from scenic coastal rides to challenging mountain trails. Whether you\'re an amateur cyclist seeking a relaxing journey or an experienced biker chasing adrenaline, Lebanon delivers unforgettable routes. Along the Mediterranean coast, roads between Batroun, Byblos, and Tyre provide smooth, sea-view rides through historic towns and lively fishing villages. Inland, areas like Aley, Baskinta, and Tannourine offer more rugged paths, winding through pine forests, terraced hillsides, and traditional mountain villages. For mountain biking enthusiasts, trails in the Chouf Biosphere Reserve, Qadisha Valley, or along sections of the Lebanon Mountain Trail provide stunning elevation changes and panoramic views. What makes cycling in Lebanon truly special is the proximity between nature and culture—you can pedal through vineyards, stop at a local bakery, or rest beside Roman ruins all in the same ride. With its moderate climate, breathtaking scenery, and welcoming communities, cycling in Lebanon is not just a sport—it\'s a soulful journey across a land where every turn of the pedal reveals new beauty and discovery.','/images/cyc.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(406,'activities','Outdoor','Skiing','Skiing in Lebanon','With six ski resorts catering to skiers and snowboarders of all skill levels, and with kilometers of backcountry and snowshoe trails waiting to be explored.','Skiing in Lebanon is a surprising yet spectacular adventure that showcases the country\'s unique geography and vibrant winter culture. Nestled in the Mount Lebanon range, Lebanon\'s ski resorts sit just an hour from the Mediterranean coast, making it one of the few places in the world where you can ski in the morning and enjoy the beach by afternoon. The largest and most developed resort is Mzaar Kfardebian, offering over 80 kilometers of trails for all skill levels, along with modern lifts, cozy chalets, and panoramic views from snowy summits. To the north, The Cedars Resort—named after the ancient cedar forests that surround it—offers higher altitudes, stunning natural beauty, and a more tranquil atmosphere perfect for nature lovers. Other resorts like Faqra, Laqlouq, and Zaarour cater to both beginners and families, with options for snowboarding, cross-country skiing, and snowshoeing. Beyond the slopes, Lebanon\'s après-ski culture is warm and inviting, featuring mountain lodges, Lebanese mezze by the fireplace, and lively nightlife in nearby towns. Skiing in Lebanon is more than a sport—it\'s a winter escape that blends natural beauty, local charm, and the thrill of alpine adventure, all under the Mediterranean sun.','/images/faraya.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(407,'activities','Cultural','Deir el Qamar','Deir el Qamar','It is an old town hemmed in an urban frame that maintained the architectural prosperities of the 17th and 18th centuries.','Deir el-Qamar is one of Lebanon\'s most enchanting and well-preserved historical villages, nestled in the heart of the Chouf Mountains. Once the capital of Mount Lebanon during the 16th to 18th centuries, this picturesque town offers a peaceful retreat into Lebanon\'s rich past and traditional charm. Walking through its cobblestone streets, visitors encounter beautifully restored stone houses with red-tiled roofs, charming courtyards, and vibrant flower gardens. The town is home to several important landmarks, including the Emir Fakhreddine II Palace, the Fakhreddine Mosque (the oldest mosque still standing in Mount Lebanon), and the Saydet el-Talle Church, a centuries-old Maronite sanctuary. Deir el-Qamar is also known for its cultural harmony, having historically hosted people of different religious backgrounds living side by side. Surrounded by lush green hills and overlooking the valley below, the town offers not only historical richness but also natural beauty. Whether you\'re enjoying a traditional Lebanese meal in a mountain restaurant, exploring heritage sites, or simply breathing in the fresh mountain air, Deir el-Qamar is a timeless destination that captures the soul of Lebanon.','/images/deir.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(408,'activities','Cultural','Beit Tabaris','Beit Tabaris','In this traditional Lebanese house, located in the heart of Ashrafieh, the objective is to host artists in residence and to offer master classes.','Beit Tabaris is a hidden gem in the heart of the Lebanese mountains, offering a peaceful escape steeped in heritage, nature, and authentic village life. Located near the town of Baskinta in the Metn region, this small traditional village is known for its serene atmosphere, stone houses, and panoramic views of the surrounding valleys and pine-covered hills. Beit Tabaris may not appear in every tourist guide, but its charm lies in its simplicity—quiet trails, blooming orchards, and a deep connection to the land. The village is a perfect starting point for hikers and nature lovers, especially those exploring the Baskinta Literary Trail, which passes through forests and landmarks tied to famous Lebanese writers and poets. Visitors to Beit Tabaris often enjoy local hospitality, homemade food, and moments of reflection in an environment untouched by mass tourism. Whether you\'re passing through on a countryside hike or staying for a quiet weekend, Beit Tabaris offers a soulful retreat into rural Lebanese life, where tradition and tranquility come together in perfect harmony.','/images/beittt.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(409,'activities','Cultural','Museum Visits','Museum Visits in Lebanon','Cultural visits in Lebanon where precious treasures from all over the world meet and tell the stories of their countries.','Museum visits in Lebanon are a fascinating journey through time, offering insight into the country\'s rich tapestry of civilizations, art, and identity. From ancient Phoenician artifacts to contemporary masterpieces, Lebanon\'s museums preserve stories that span thousands of years. The most iconic is the National Museum of Beirut, home to a vast collection of archaeological treasures, including sarcophagi, mosaics, and relics from the Phoenician, Roman, Byzantine, and Ottoman eras. For those interested in more focused themes, the Sursock Museum in Beirut offers a deep dive into modern and contemporary Lebanese art, housed in a stunning 19th-century villa that blends Venetian and Ottoman architecture. In Byblos, the Byblos Fossil Museum showcases incredibly preserved marine fossils dating back over 100 million years, while in the mountains of Beiteddine, the Moussa Castle Museum tells the romantic story of one man\'s dream to build a medieval-style fortress by hand. Each museum in Lebanon tells a unique story—whether through the lens of history, art, or folklore—and offers a deeper understanding of the country\'s diverse cultural heritage. With every visit, you don\'t just view objects behind glass—you step into the narrative of a land that has always been a crossroads of civilizations.','/images/crystals.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(410,'activities','Cultural','Festivals and Celebrations','Festivals and Celebrations in Lebanon','Classical music, dance, theater, opera, and jazz as well as modern world music are performed all around the regions in Lebanon.','Festivals and celebrations in Lebanon are a vibrant expression of the country\'s cultural richness, artistic creativity, and deep-rooted sense of community. Throughout the year, cities, towns, and villages come alive with events that blend music, dance, tradition, and joy. Some of the most renowned festivals include the Beiteddine Art Festival, held in a stunning 19th-century palace in the Chouf mountains, where international and local artists perform under the stars, and the Byblos International Festival, which transforms the ancient port city into a magical stage by the sea. In Baalbek, one of the oldest Roman sites in the world, music echoes through ancient stone as part of the Baalbek International Festival, attracting global performers to its historic temples. Beyond the major cultural festivals, Lebanon also celebrates religious and seasonal events with passion and warmth. From Eid and Christmas celebrations to Independence Day parades, and wine and food festivals in the Bekaa Valley, each occasion is marked with music, traditional food, and heartfelt gatherings. Whether you\'re dancing dabke in a village square or attending an orchestral concert in a Roman temple, festivals in Lebanon offer unforgettable moments where history, art, and community come together in celebration.','/images/fest.webp',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
